sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant U as User
    participant TH as Dashboard Thread UI
    participant PG as new-chat page.tsx
    participant API as POST /api/v1/new_chat
    participant TASK as stream_new_chat
  participant AG as Main Chat Agent
  participant TLS as Common Tools
    participant DB as Postgres / SearchSpace

    U->>TH: Type question + optional @mentions/images
    TH->>PG: onSubmit -> aui.composer().send()

    alt First question in fresh chat
        PG->>DB: createThread(search_space_id, "New Chat")
        DB-->>PG: thread_id
        PG->>TH: Update URL /dashboard/{space}/new-chat/{thread_id}
    end

    PG->>TH: Add optimistic user message (msg-user-*)
    PG->>API: POST new_chat payload
    Note over PG,API: includes user_query, chat_id, search_space_id,\nmessage history, mentions, disabled_tools, user_images

    API->>API: Check thread, permissions, and file mode
    API->>TASK: Start stream_new_chat(...)
    TASK->>DB: Persist user turn + assistant shell
    TASK->>AG: Build agent (model + tools + middleware)

    AG->>TLS: Typical call: search_surfsense_docs
    TLS-->>AG: Knowledge hits / citations
    AG->>TLS: read_file, glob/grep/ls (when needed)
    TLS-->>AG: Matching files / text snippets
    AG->>TLS: web_search then scrape_webpage (if needed)
    TLS-->>AG: Web results + page content
    AG->>TLS: generate_report (if user asks for output)
    TLS-->>AG: Report id / status

    TASK-->>PG: SSE stream (text/analysis/tool events)
    PG->>TH: Live UI updates + tool cards + thinking steps
    TASK-->>PG: data-user-message-id / data-assistant-message-id
    PG->>TH: Rename optimistic IDs to canonical msg-{db_id}
    TASK-->>PG: data-token-usage + data-action-log + data-turn-info

    alt Interrupt needed (permission / HITL)
        TASK-->>PG: data-interrupt-request
        PG->>TH: Show interrupt UI and pause
        TH->>PG: User decisions
        PG->>API: POST /api/v1/threads/{id}/resume-chat
        API->>TASK: stream_resume_chat(...)
        TASK-->>PG: Resume SSE until completion
    end

    TASK->>DB: finalize_assistant_turn (always-run cleanup)
    TASK-->>PG: Final SSE completion
    PG->>TH: Final rendered answer + persisted thread state

    alt User cancels mid-stream
        TH->>PG: Cancel run
        PG->>API: POST /api/v1/threads/{id}/cancel-active-turn
        API-->>TASK: Mark turn cancelling
        TASK-->>PG: turn-status / graceful stop events
    else Pre-accept failure
        API-->>PG: HTTP error before stream accepted
        PG->>TH: Roll back optimistic user msg + show error
    end
